reviews.title: Review of Burn It Down Festival 2022
Review of Burn It Down Festival 2022
reviews.body: A great little festival giving up and coming bands a platform to show their talent. Me and my other half have been to burn it down 3 times now and have seen bands playing at this festival increase in popularity, BID are clearly very good at picking out growing bands. Venue (foundry) is fantastic also - well laid out and the attic is an absolute sweat fest! Looking forward to next year!

reviews.title: Review of Burn It Down Festival 2022
Review of Burn It Down Festival 2022
Review of Burn It Down Festival 2022
reviews.body: Amazing festival with a great mix of bands

reviews.title: Review of Burn It Down Festival 2022
reviews.body: Best festival this year. Crowd all very playful and friendly, music loud, best value for money ever. Line-up forced me to drive 5 hours each way.

reviews.title: Review of Burn It Down Festival 2022
Review of Burn It Down Festival 2022
Review of Burn It Down Festival 2022
reviews.body: Great value festival, discovered so many new bands, definitely come again and shout out to the security in foundry they did a top top job

reviews.title: Review of Burn It Down Festival 2022
reviews.body: Very well organised and great location as venues were within a minute walk of each other. Brilliant diverse line up including lots of female/non-binary fronted acts.

faqs.question: When is Burn It Down Festival 2023?
faqs.answer: Burn It Down Festival will take place on a Friday 8th - Sunday 10th September 2023

faqs.question: What happens if I bought a ticket and cannot attend?
faqs.answer: Unfortunately we can’t issue you with a refund if you can’t make the event due to work commitments or your mates have dropped out. In these circumstances, we advise passing on your tickets privately to avoid losing out on the money spent. Refunds can only be offered if the event is cancelled or postponed, as agreed upon purchase.

faqs.question: Where will Burn It Down Festival take place?
faqs.answer:
Burn It Down Festival will take place at The Foundry in Torquay and will be the largest indoor alternative festival in the South West.

Address: 11 Torwood St, Torquay TQ1 1ED.

faqs.question: Does Burn It Down Festival have any age restrictions?
faqs.answer: You must be over the age of 14 to attend Burn It Down Festival.

news.title: Burn It Down Festival to host UK's hottest alternative talents this September
news.summary: The south-wests largest indoor festival returns to see out the summer season, showcasing some of the UK alternative scene's best rock, metal and hardcore acts
